<subSubSection pageId="94" pageNumber="852" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="94.[2061,2656,749,1175]" lastBlockId="94.[1445,2659,1183,2165]" pageId="94" pageNumber="852">
Taxonomic status of 
<taxonomicName box="[2373,2558,827,860]" pageId="94" pageNumber="852">Epfesicus tater</taxonomicName>
is uncertain, and it has been suggested to be a synonym or subspecies of E. nilsson, although additional samples are needed to confirm this conclusion because distribution of E. tate: is so disconnected from that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Keyserling &amp; Blasius" authorityYear="1839" box="[2168,2316,1063,1096]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Vesperus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="94" pageNumber="852" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nilssonii">E. nilssonii</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[2332,2448,1063,1096]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="94" pageNumber="852" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Eptesicus</taxonomicName>
tater was originally named 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blyth" authorityYear="1863" box="[2255,2485,1103,1136]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Nycticeius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="94" pageNumber="852" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="atratus">Nycticeius atratus</taxonomicName>
by E. Blyth in 1863, but this name was preoccupied by 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blyth" authorityYear="1863" box="[1450,1673,1183,1216]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Amblyotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="94" pageNumber="852" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="atratus">Amblyotis atratus</taxonomicName>
by F. Kolenati in 1858 (synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Keyserling &amp; Blasius" authorityYear="1839" box="[2193,2339,1183,1216]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Vesperus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="94" pageNumber="852" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nilssonii">E. nilssonii</taxonomicName>
) and was renamed by J. R. Ellerman and T. C. S. Morrison-Scott in 1951. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
